Title: mk_jolokia: allow import of integer values for timeout values
Class: fix
Compatible: compat
Component: checks
Date: 1730721264
Edition: cre
Level: 1
Version: 2.2.0p37

Values for <code>timeout</code> when configuring a bakery rule for "JMX monitoring of Java JVMs using Jolokia"
have to be floating point, resulting in <code>ValueError</code> when integer values are configured instead.

This change introduces a migration rule for <code>timeout</code> turning all numbers into <code>float</code>.
